The ATLAS detector [1] consists of an inner tracking system surrounded by a superconducting solenoid, electromagnetic (EM) and hadronic (HAD) calorimeters, and a muon spectrometer. The inner detector is immersed in a 2 T axial magnetic field, and consists of pixel and silicon microstrip detectors inside a transition radiation tracker, which together provide charged-particle tracking in the region |η|<2.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
