				\begin{document}$$\pi ^0 _\mathrm{cand}$$\end{document}’s. The excellent resolution of these decays leads to a superior overall core resolution. Misreconstructed decays have the poorest resolution and result in larger tails. In particular, misestimation of the number of πcand0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
