				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\pi ^0 _\mathrm{cand}$$\end{document}’s leads to a bias of up to 25 %. Decays containing neutral kaons exhibit a large low-energy bias because at least some of their energy is typically missed by the reconstruction.

